##
## Plans
##
@node plans "Plans"

 I released this working but not complete version because there is a lack
 of AGA support in the screen blanker arena, and I wouldn't want someone
 to feel that there was not enough support for the new AGA machines. After
 all, a screen blanker is an important thing. How else could we impress
 the Macintosh users :).

 As soon as I get over the fact that Commodore designed their shared
 libraries in a poor manner (read: stupidly, in my opinion), I'll probably
 come up with a reasonable and standard method for writing modules at which
 point I'll release the source code and examples on how to write your own
 Blanker modules. Also, I'll most likely have written a number of other
 modules to go along with the distribution so that non-programming people
 can enjoy this blanker as well.
@endnode
